Long Post:  I’ve been back in Baltimore for 7 days now and was excited to come back to feel the vibes and love I’d missed so much. Sadly a lot of those relationships has changed with friends and even with family so most of my time home has been spent alone. To the point I feel like I’m bothering folks if I ask for anything, even if it’s a simple link up.

I was even told “you can’t leave and come back with expectations from people”. That woke me up and made me realize a lot because I don’t know all the experiences people have been having that led to whatever growth that did or did not come with it. All I can do is recognize and accept the fact that we’re at different parts of our process in this thing called life and NOT SAYING one is greater than the other it just is what it is.

I feel like people often wait for you to do “that next big thing”. Meanwhile I’m just enjoying the process I’m in that’s preparing me for whatever it is.

📸: @tevin_towns

This is me seeing the bright side of things 🙃 lol

But on a serious note it’s definitely a patience builder!

Last year and a half has been rocky since I moved to LA.
I allowed multiple things and circumstances to slow me down from my objective. Some of it came from intimidation, imposter syndrome, and a host of other feelings.

Then the other day I got invited to do an interview for a Church Podcast and they asked me about my journey and what role did God play in it. 

I never told my whole story up to this point and halfway through I broke down in tears (like gasping for air crying lol) because all I could think was “DAMN, through all of that I’m still going 

and may have questioned God but not one time did I feel like she left my side, no matter how dark it got. So why am I now allowing this present adversity to have an affect as if God and I haven’t conquered it before!

This is me, sharing a message for myself with whom ever else may need or want to hear it ! 

#motivation #affirmations
Instagram can get clouded with false realities, but I enjoy sharing my truths more. #motivation #affirmations

TD Jakes once said “we don’t know how good good feels, until we’ve felt bad.”

Embrace those moments and trust that they are prepping you to not only receive but be able to maintain what’s to come! #motivation #affirmations #NoTestNoTestimony

A lot of people don’t know the story of “I don’t wanna be a playa” or the adventures we had creating and selling the mixtape after.

But the short of it all is that hearing a 1 minute freestyle turned into a 9 year brotherhood. We shared ideas, dreams, our love for the city, shit I even remember the day we linked and he couldn’t stop talking because his crush ( now mother of his child) finally gave him a chance 😂.

To know Davo was to love him because no matter how hard life got he persevered and always found a way to smile through it, and I mean ALWAYS! 

And yea no one is perfect but I promise y’all this man did way more good than bad and I’m crushed because I know the role he played in my life and watched the role he played in others and someone just cut that off. 

I love you brother, thank you for the timeless art, priceless memories and will forever send prayers to your family.
Don’t worry about it sweetheart, this that SPLAHHH!
Take some time to pray for someone else ❤️
